# Racial Justice {-}

Police are generally more apt to use heavy responses including chemical weapons against Black protesters in general.
It is therefore not surprising to learn that law enforcement use foggers to deploy chemical weapons on racial justice protests.
Indeed, the first use of the fogger in the United States was during the [Liberty City Riots](#MiamiFL1968_08_08), a police action in response to Black community organizations holding conversation among themselves.

The most recent 

## Danville IL, Aug 10 1969 {-}

Danville Police used a pepper fogger to disperse a crowd of Black protesters that had used picnic tables to barricade a street through their neighborhood on a second night of demonstrations [@AP1969a].

